verses.text: Then the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* answered Job out of the whirlwind , and said ,
Who \add is\add* this that darkeneth counsel by words without knowledge ?
Gird up now thy loins like a man ; for I will demand of thee, and answer thou me.\f + \fr 38.3 \ft answer…: Heb. make me know\f* \p
Where wast thou when I laid the foundations of the earth ? declare , if thou hast understanding.\f + \fr 38.4 \ft hast…: Heb. knowest understanding\f*
Who hath laid the measures thereof, if thou knowest ? or who hath stretched the line upon it?
Whereupon are the foundations thereof fastened ? or who laid the corner stone thereof;\f + \fr 38.6 \ft foundations: Heb. sockets\f*\f + \fr 38.6 \ft fastened: Heb. made to sink?\f*
When the morning stars sang together , and all the sons of God shouted for joy?
Or \add who\add* shut up the sea with doors , when it brake forth , \add as if\add* it had issued out of the womb ?
When I made the cloud the garment thereof, and thick darkness a swaddlingband for it,
And brake up for it my decreed \add place\add*, and set bars and doors ,\f + \fr 38.10 \ft brake…: or, established my decree upon it\f*
And said , Hitherto shalt thou come , but no further : and here shall thy proud waves be stayed ?\f + \fr 38.11 \ft thy…: Heb. the pride of thy waves\f* \p
Hast thou commanded the morning since thy days ; \add and\add* caused the dayspring to know his place ;
That it might take hold of the ends of the earth , that the wicked might be shaken out of it?\f + \fr 38.13 \ft ends: Heb. wings\f*
It is turned as clay \add to\add* the seal ; and they stand as a garment.
And from the wicked their light is withholden , and the high arm shall be broken.
Hast thou entered into the springs of the sea ? or hast thou walked in the search of the depth ?
Have the gates of death been opened unto thee? or hast thou seen the doors of the shadow of death ?
Hast thou perceived the breadth of the earth ? declare if thou knowest it all.
Where \add is\add* the way \add where\add* light dwelleth ? and \add as for\add* darkness , where \add is\add* the place thereof,
That thou shouldest take it to the bound thereof, and that thou shouldest know the paths \add to\add* the house thereof?\f + \fr 38.20 \ft to the bound: or, at, etc\f*
Knowest thou \add it\add*, because thou wast then born ? or \add because\add* the number of thy days \add is\add* great ?
Hast thou entered into the treasures of the snow ? or hast thou seen the treasures of the hail ,
Which I have reserved against the time of trouble , against the day of battle and war ?
By what way is the light parted , \add which\add* scattereth the east wind upon the earth ? \p
Who hath divided a watercourse for the overflowing of waters , or a way for the lightning of thunder ;
To cause it to rain on the earth , \add where\add* no man \add is; on\add* the wilderness , wherein \add there is\add* no man ;
To satisfy the desolate and waste \add ground;\add* and to cause the bud of the tender herb to spring forth ?
Hath the rain a father ? or who hath begotten the drops of dew ?
Out of whose womb came the ice ? and the hoary frost of heaven , who hath gendered it?
The waters are hid as \add with\add* a stone , and the face of the deep is frozen.\f + \fr 38.30 \ft is…: Heb. is taken\f*
Canst thou bind the sweet influences of Pleiades , or loose the bands of Orion ?\f + \fr 38.31 \ft Pleiades: or, the seven stars: Heb. Cimah\f*\f + \fr 38.31 \ft Orion: Heb. Cesil?\f*
Canst thou bring forth Mazzaroth in his season ? or canst thou guide Arcturus with his sons ?\f + \fr 38.32 \ft Mazzaroth: or, the twelve signs\f*\f + \fr 38.32 \ft guide: Heb. guide them\f*
Knowest thou the ordinances of heaven ? canst thou set the dominion thereof in the earth ?
Canst thou lift up thy voice to the clouds , that abundance of waters may cover thee?
Canst thou send lightnings , that they may go , and say unto thee, Here we \add are\add*?\f + \fr 38.35 \ft Here…: Heb. Behold us?\f*
Who hath put wisdom in the inward parts ? or who hath given understanding to the heart ?
Who can number the clouds in wisdom ? or who can stay the bottles of heaven ,\f + \fr 38.37 \ft stay: Heb. cause to lie down\f*
When the dust groweth into hardness , and the clods cleave fast together ?\f + \fr 38.38 \ft groweth…: or, is turned into mire: Heb. is poured\f*
Wilt thou hunt the prey for the lion ? or fill the appetite of the young lions ,\f + \fr 38.39 \ft the appetite: Heb. the life\f*
When they couch in \add their\add* dens , \add and\add* abide in the covert to lie in wait ?
Who provideth for the raven his food ? when his young ones cry unto God , they wander for lack of meat.
